SURVEY TITLE: Clinical Consult Intake Form
SURVEY DESCRIPTION: The purpose of these questions is to help the medical team identify risk factors for certain diseases based on your health history, your family health history, and your current lifestyle. Based on the information you provide here and during your Clinic visit, in addition to your genetic information, you and the clinician can work together to come up with a plan for your care. To learn more, read What to Expect at a Total Health Virtual Consultation.

Please answer the following questions about your personal and family health history to the best of your knowledge.

    [ ] Kidney disease (examples: chronic kidney disease, kidney stones, gout)

    [ ] Gastrointestinal conditions (examples: celiac disease, diverticulitis, inflammatory bowel disease, irritable bowel syndrome, gallstones, metabolic associated steatotic hepatitis also known as nonalcoholic fatty liver disease (NAFLD) or nonalcoholic steatotic hepatitis (NASH))    
    [ ] Lung disease (examples: alpha-1-antitrypsin deficiency, asthma)    
    [ ] Diabetes (examples: type 1 or type 2, gestational diabetes or diabetes during pregnancy, high blood sugar)    
    [ ] Autoimmune conditions (examples: thyroid disorders, fibromyalgia, rheumatoid arthritis)    
    [ ] Skin conditions (examples: eczema, psoriasis, rosacea, basal cell or squamous cell skin cancer)    
    [ ] Vision and hearing loss conditions (examples: deafness, macular degeneration, glaucoma)    
    [ ] Known or suspected inherited or genetic conditions (examples: cystic fibrosis, sickle cell disease, hereditary hemochromatosis)    
    [ ] Adverse reactions to drugs or medications
